on ss, Nickel\nPlate 4 1 2 s, Inland Steel 4' 2 s, Standard\nOil of New Jersey ss. Columbia Gas ss,\nUtah Power Light 5s and Interna-\nTelephone 5s all sagged.\nUnited States Government securities\nwere moderately active and firm, re\nsponding to the Treasury offering of\n$125,000,000 of 91-day discount bills.\nThese are expected to b? sold at a\nrecord low price and there was some\nswitching into long-term issues as a\nresult.\nConvertible bonds were weak, with\ndrops in Alleghany ss. Baltimore Ohio\n4>is, Chicago <fc Northwestern 4%5,\nAtchison 4 'is, American Telephone\n4 1 *s, Texas Corporation 5s and Gen\neral Theaters Equipment 6s.\nWashington Stock Exchange\nSALES.\nWashington Gas 6s \u201cA\u201d\u2014$1,000 at 103,\n$1 000 at 1025a.\nWashington Loan Trust Co.\u2014lo at\n450.\nLanston Monotype\u2014lo at 100, 10 at 100,\n10 at 100, 10 at 100, 10 at 100. 10 at\n100, 10 at 100, 10 at 100, 10 at 100,\n10 at 100.\nI Mergenthaler Linotype\u2014lo at\nThe Carpel Corp.\u2014s at 22! a, 50 at 21%.\nAFTER CALL.\nCapital Traction Co.\u2014lo at 50, 5 at 50,\n2 at 50.\nWashington Gas 6s \"A\u201d\u2014s4,ooo at\n102%, 200 at 103.\nPotomac Electric 6% pfd\u20144 at 110 1 2\nWashington Gas 6s \u201cB\u201d\u2014$100 at 105 _*.\nFederal-American com.\u20142s at 30, 30\nat 30.\nMergenthaler Linotype\u2014s at 90.\nCapital Traction Co.\u20142 at 50.\nUNLISTED DEPARTMENT.\nChapin Sacks 8% pfd.\u20143o at 103 s#. 5\nBid and Asked Prices.\nBONDS.\nPUBLIC UTILITY.\nBid. Asked.\nAmer. Tel. Sc Trisa. 4%s \u201933 102\nAmer. Tel At Trlea. 4%s '3D... 142%\nAm. Tel. Sc Tel. ctl. tr. 5s 105*.\nAnacostia At Pot. R. R. 5s 82 83\nAna. At Pot guar 6s 95 98\nCAP. Tel. of Va. 5k 102\nCapital Traction R. R. 5s 85 87\nCity At Suburban 5s 80 82\nGeorgetown Gas Ist 5s 103'/a\nPotomac Elec. cons. 5% 102 3\nPotomac Elec. 6s 1953 107 110\nWash.. Alex At Mt. Vernon ctf. 2\nWash.. Balto. Anr.ap 5s 35 41\nWashington Gas 5s 104 a 106\nWash. Gas 6s, series A 102' t 103'4\nWash. Gas 6s. series B 105 1